"{\"uid\": \"rte.ie-sport-paris-2024-2024-0729-1462490-olympics-podcast-holy-mona-ireland-win-first-medal\", \"text\": \"  On a super night for Irish swimming, Mikey Stafford is joined by Mona McSharry's fellow University of Tennessee alumni Barry Murphy to relive the Sligo star's bronze swim.  Minutes after the race, Murphy was still recovering from the nail-biting ending as McSharry took the bronze by 0.01 seconds from TWO others in the 100m breaststroke final.  He also pays credit to the progress in Irish swimming, which may see another medal won on Tuesday when Daniel Wiffen goes in the 800m freestyle final.  Following Kellie Harrington's imperious opening bout, Eric Donovan joins Mikey from Paris to discuss the Tokyo gold medallist's fine form and look ahead to the rest of the week for an Irish team that has several shots on boxing medals.  Eric also explains the scoring method now used in the case of a fight that finishes level on the judges' cards.  And Mikey shares the story of Australia boxer Reginald Snowy Baker, who knew a thing or two about dodgy officiating.  Listen to the RT\\u00c9 Olympics Podcast on theRT\\u00c9 Radio Player,Apple Podcasts,Spotify, orwherever you get your podcasts  We need your consent to load this rte-player contentWe use rte-player to manage extra content that can set cookies on your device and collect data about your activity. Please review their details and accept them to load the content.Manage Preferences    \\u00a9 RT\\u00c9 2026. RT\\u00c9.ie is the website of Raidi\\u00f3 Teilif\\u00eds \\u00c9ireann, Ireland's National Public Service Media. RT\\u00c9 is not responsible for the content of external internet sites.  Images Courtesy of Getty Images.\"}"